				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Primary/secondary combos<a name="38370"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 5 04 2:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>How far are you from epic?  That'll help immensely.
<br />

<br />
Aside from that, like the previous posters said, get a clicky invis item, or get used to switching instruments.  I did the latter, and really, it's not all that bad once you get in the swing of things.  Since you're using a TDoK, I'd recommend getting a primary-equippable flute, so's you can just make two spots in your hotkey bank.  One with your primary inventory slot, and one right next to it on the bank that's general inventory, and holds your &quot;spare&quot; instrument.
<br />

<br />
Remember, it only checks for your wind instrument at the END of the song, so you can start it, then switch.
<br />

<br />
Good luck!</span></td>
